2.00	National_Union_of_Mine_and_Metal_Workers_of_the_Mexican_Republic	National Union of Mine and Metal Workers of the Mexican Republic	The National Union of Mine and Metal Workers of the Mexican Republic (Spanish: , or SNTMMSRM) is a union of coal and copper miners, as well as iron and steel workers, in Mexico. It was founded in 1934, and in 1936 it became an affiliate of the newly formed Confederation of Mexican Workers (CTM).	
